1. *Žuriš* li ti da stigneš na sastanak na vreme? (Are you in a hurry to arrive at the meeting on time?)
2. Nema potrebe da se *žuriš*, imamo dovoljno vremena. (There's no need to hurry, we have enough time.)
3. Ona uvek *žuri* i zbog toga kasni na sastanke. (She always hurries and that's why she's late for meetings.)
4. Da li *žurite* da završite ovaj projekat do kraja nedelje? (Are you in a hurry to finish this project by the end of the week?)
5. Molim te, *žuri* se, već smo kasni za predstavu. (Please hurry up, we're already late for the show.)
6. Nemoj da *žuriš* s tom odlukom, dobro razmisli pre nego što doneseš konačnu odluku. (Don't hurry with that decision, think carefully before you make a final decision.)
7. Sada nije vreme da se *žurimo*, moramo biti pažljivi i uraditi sve kako treba. (Now is not the time to hurry, we need to be careful and do everything properly.)
8. Vidim da ti se *žuri*, ali moramo prekontrolisati ovaj izveštaj pre nego što ga pošaljemo klijentu. (I see that you're in a hurry, but we need to double-check this report before sending it to the client.)
9. Kako se *žuriš*, samo ćeš napraviti grešku. (As you rush, you'll only make a mistake.)
10. Zbog loših vremenskih uslova, ljudi su se počeli *žuriti* kući pre kraja radnog vremena. (Due to bad weather conditions, people started hurrying home before the end of the workday.)